2017 WW27 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 BKC Release Announcement (\r\n BKC #24)

\r\n \r\n \r\n

DEG Platform Integration Team

\r\n \r\n
\r\n

The DEG platform Integration team announces the release of 2017 WW27 Purley-FPGA Server SKX H0/LBG B1 BKC release package for Intel internal use. The release is based on OS of\r\n \r\n RHEL7.3\r\n server. The auto-installer packages are available in the Artifactory server (both SH site and OR site). Any questions please contact Li, Feng Y.

\r\n

Purley FPGA (RP Board: Neon City FPGA)

  • Total test\r\ncases: 110;\r\nPassed test cases is 105 and pass rate is 95.45%. 
  •  Test\r\ncoverage:  

SKX-FPGA H0\r\nVIS/LBG-4 B1: Run full\r\nBKC test case  and P&P test

SKX-FPGA H0 VIS/LBG-T B1: Run\r\nQAT test case

SKX-FPGA B0 ES2/LBG-4 B1: Run\r\nboot up test and AAL test case

\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n

  • Power cycling\r\n(G3/S5/Warm-reboot) are not covered in BKC test due to the key sighting 5345509,  FPGA\r\nteam is working on the fix.

P&P Update:

1. Changed CPU from B0 to H0 for power and performance test from WW04.

2. Run NLB with Linux kernel 4.7.0, other tests are running with Linux Kernel 3.10.0

3. Runing NLB GBS mode 0 lpbk1 to exercise 2 sockets simultaneously for NLB loading power test.

4. Target for all test items are not ready, But OSS need target to generate report, so we just use WW43\'s data as target.

5. FPGA power workload: NLB

6. Core performance workloads: Mlc, Linpack, Stream.

WW27:

HSD:[5346307] MLC local idle latency score dropped around 9%, caused by BIOS  CL# 510309

Known Issue/Errata:

\xc2\xb7        5345546 [2016_WW45 BKC][BIOS:107_D07][Neon city FPGA]WOL function is still working when disabled in BIOS.  

Status:  No fix . Purley-FPGA is aligned with Purley-2S/4S Launch collateral. Details can be found 5345546 in HSD

 

\xc2\xb7        5345493 [2016_WW43 BKC][BIOS:105_D11][Neon city FPGA] Entering "Platform Configuration -> PCH Configuration" resets other saved change. 

Status:  No fix . Purley-FPGA is aligned with Purley2S/4S Launch collateral. Details can be found 5345493 in HSD

 

 5345843 [2017_WW03 BKC][BIOS:118_R01][Neon city FPGA] P3V3 voltage on Purley-FPGA boards is 1.1V when system under S5 state 

Status: No fix. Details can be found 5345843 in HSD
